'''Banca Popolare di Crema''' is an Italian banking brand and former subsidiary of [[Banco Popolare]]. ==History== Founded as '''Banca Popolare Agricola di Mutuo Credito''' in 1870, the Crema-based bank was later known as '''Banca Popolare di Crema'''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bancopopolare.it/banca-popolare-di-crema/la-storia/|title=La Storia|access-date=21 December 2016|publisher=Banco Popolare|language=Italian}}</ref> It became a subsidiary [[Banca Popolare di Lodi]] (via sub-holding [[Reti Bancarie]] from 2003 to 2006) and then as a subsidiary of [[Banco Popolare]] since 2007. In 2011, Banca Popolare di Crema was absorbed by Banco Popolare,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gruppobancopopolare.it/media/2011-08-29_ProgettoGrandeBP_FusioneInc-BPCrema_Progetto-di-Fusione-per-incorporazione-nel-Banco-di-BP-Crema.pdf|title=Progetto di Fusione per incorporazione nel Banco di BP Crema|date=29 August 2011|access-date=21 December 2016|publisher=Banco Popolare|language=Italian}}</ref> but retained as a brand, under banking division Banca Popolare di Lodi.
As at 31 December 2010, BP Crema had a shareholders' equity of €214.819&nbsp;million.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gruppobancopopolare.it/media/2011-06-30_ProgettoGrandeBP_FusioneInc-BPCrema_Situazioni-Patrimoniali-ex-art-2501-quater-cc.zip|title=Situazioni Patrimoniali ex art. 2501 quater c.c.|date=2011|access-date=21 December 2016|publisher=Banco Popolare|language=Italian}}</ref> ==References== {{reflist|30em}} ==External links== * {{official website|http://www.popcrema.it}}
