'''Ole Christian Bach''' (31 May 1957 – 11 July 2005) was a [[Norway|Norwegian]] [[con artist]].
In 1988, he was convicted on charges of fraud and sentenced to 4 years in [[prison]].<ref name="Local">{{cite news|url=http://www.thelocal.se/1723/20050712/|title=Millionaire shoots himself after police chase|date=12 July 2005|work=[[The Local]]|accessdate=23 December 2010}}</ref> He was convicted again for his involvement with the theft and sale of [[Edvard Munch]]'s ''[[Madonna (Edvard Munch)|Madonna]]'' in 1992,<ref name="Local"/> and sentenced to 7 months in prison. Bach managed to establish new connections, most importantly with [[Gerard Cok]]. Cok controlled the German porn enterprise [[Beate Uhse]], and he trusted Bach with the establishment of porn shops in Norway and Sweden.<ref>[http://www.vg.no/nyheter/innenriks/bach-saken/dette-var-ole-christian-bach/a/283651/ "Dette var Ole Christian Bach"], Per Valebrok in ''[[Verdens Gang|VG]]'' 12.7.2005</ref> With security in an estate out of Oslo, Cok also gave Bach a NOK 60.000.000 loan. The security later turned out to be only in the estate's boat house.<ref name="Hegnar">"[http://www.hegnar.no/okonomi/politikk/artikkel115735.ece Pornomilliardæren saksøker Bachs advokat]" Haugen in Hegnar.no 1.10.2007</ref>
In 2005 he was again charged with economic [[fraud]]. On 11 July 2005, he committed [[suicide]] in [[Sweden]] after a car chase with Swedish undercover police.<ref name="Local"/>
==Aftermath== After Bach's death, Gerhard Cok sued Ole Christian Bach's lawyer [[Ronny Mulstad]] for his role in securing Cok's loan to Bach.<ref name="Hegnar"/> The dispute was settled outside court.<ref>"[http://www.nettavisen.no/nyheter/forlik-for-bach-advokat/1851006.html Forlik for Bach-advokat]" ''[[Nettavisen]]'' 9.10.2006</ref>
The role of the journalists who covered the Bach's hiding came under investigation after Bach's death. One journalist was fined for having helped Bach to avoid arrest by paying him for interviews.<ref>"Bot til journalist for å ha bistått person på flukt fra politiet", [http://www.okokrim.no/id/E8EAB738B5C0C3D8C1257589003C9251 Økokrim 23.1.2008] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150923085822/http://www.okokrim.no/id/E8EAB738B5C0C3D8C1257589003C9251 |date=2015-09-23 }}</ref> A magazine was fined for similar reasons.<ref>"Bot til ukeblad-forlag for å ha bistått person på flukt fra politiet" [http://www.okokrim.no/id/D8FBF78CBC54FF61C12576490026339F Økokrim 8.10.2009] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150923085730/http://www.okokrim.no/id/D8FBF78CBC54FF61C12576490026339F |date=2015-09-23 }}</ref>
A friend of Bach's was sentenced to prison for helping Bach to avoid arrest.<ref>"Dømt til fengsel for å ha bistått med å skjule Bach mens han var på flukt fra politiet" [http://www.okokrim.no/id/CC47B2A57DD1DF13C12575DF003736F2 Økokrims nyhetsarkiv 9.10.2006] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150923085826/http://www.okokrim.no/id/CC47B2A57DD1DF13C12575DF003736F2 |date=2015-09-23 }}</ref>
